Implemented end-to-end per your workflow, with strict TDD and a commit.

- Added new signal policy module with production behavior in `src/signal_policy.rs`:
  - NS-003 revoke-on-exit trigger policy
  - NS-011/066/067 TTL bounds (`min=60s`, `max=12h` default) + missing TTL rejection
  - NS-014 idempotent revocation classification (`already revoked` / `expired` treated as success)
  - NS-026 forwarding policy (`SIGTERM/SIGHUP/SIGINT` forward, `SIGPIPE` ignored) + default 30s grace
  - NS-027 revocation budget defaults (`10s`, `500ms`, `3 retries`) + `budget=0` disable behavior + exponential backoff
  - NS-028 double-signal escalation behavior
  - NS-029 parallel multi-credential revocation with failure isolation and per-credential budget handling
- Wired mint TTL validation to shared policy in `src/mint.rs` and exported module in `src/lib.rs`.
- Added dedicated rule-named tests (at least one per NS rule, plus extra edge cases from review) in `tests/signal_handling_policy.rs`.
- Added offline provenance draft at `.beads/provenance-drafts/noscope-mpl.md`.

Linus-style self-review findings/fixes applied:
- Fixed `SIGPIPE` path so it does not start shutdown.
- Implemented real budget-aware retry logic (instead of ignoring budget).
- Added edge-case tests for budget-zero disable and retry-until-success behavior.

Verification run:
- `cargo test` (red phase first: failed as expected before implementation)
- `cargo test --test signal_handling_policy`
- `cargo test`
- `cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings`
- `cargo test && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings`

